Job Responsibilities

Providing receptionist service, handling telephone calls, courier services;
Handling office supplies, place order and stock keeping;
Responsible for general duties of HR, maintain attendance records in the personnel files;
Office administrative support to Maintenance & Repair;
Capable to handle correspondence and multitask independently;
Co-ordinate and support scheduled activities;
Assist in ad hoc duties as assigned.

Job Requirements

Diploma or above;
At least 2 years of experience in office administration, related to insurance office is preferred;
Proficiency in Microsoft Office applications;
Good command of both spoken and written English and Mandarin;
Good communication and interpersonal skills;
Independent and able to work under pressure;
Immediately available is highly preferred.

We offer 5-day week, competitive remuneration package, and good career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your resume with EXPECTED SALARY by clicking “APPLY NOW”. All personal data collected would be used for recruitment purpose only)

Responsibilities and Requirements：
University degree or accredited insurance professional qualification;
Mainly responsible for policy administration and daily operation support;
2 - 3 years of relevant work experience, applicant with property insurance experience will be advantage;
Proficient in Chinese and English spoken and written expressions;
Good interpersonal and communication skills;
Self-motivated, independent, able to work under pressure.

We offer competitive remuneration package. Interested parties, please send your resume with CURRENT & EXPECTED salary and DATE AVAILABLE by clicking 'Apply Now'.

(Data collected would be used for recruitment purpose only）

Job Descriptions

Manage full spectrum of recruitment services, including but not limited to interviewing candidates, understanding their' needs, assessing and identifying the right candidates;
Translate business requirements into recruitment practices and deliver solutions aligned with business objectives;
Source and evaluate the effectiveness of advertising and recruitment channel;
Responsible for sales management of the team including hiring, training and performance evaluation.

 Job Requirements

Bachelor’s degree holder, with major in relevant sector preferable;
Possess excellent presentation and influencing skills to advise candidate at all levels in a professional manner;
Excellent command in English, Mandarin and Cantonese.

 Benefits

Basic salary up to 25,000 + competitive commission;
Comprehensive training programs;
Excellent career path;
Remuneration negotiable.

Candidates without recruitment or sales experience but have the right motivation and attitude are welcomed. Training will be provided.

Responsibilities

Analyze and valuate a wide range of financial products, including but not limited to bonds, structure notes, other structured products, etc;
Prepare daily P&L reporting, Calculate P&Ls of different investment pools;
Coordinate with internal stakeholders including front desk, Risk Department on the development of valuation model;
Participate in related valuation system enhancement projects;
Produce daily and quarterly product control reports to management;
Ad-hoc analysis and PNL reporting as needed;
Handle other ad-hoc tasks as assigned by Financial Controller.
Requirement

Degree holder, major in accounting or other finance related subjects
Minimum 5 years’ work experience in the field of Product Control in sizable financial institutions;
Familiar with the valuation of different financial products, especially in Fixed Income Products (bonds, structure notes, etc);
Strong & Solid knowledge on financial instruments & market operations
Proficient in setting up valuation model;
Independent, strong analytical abilities and communication skill, good time management and high attention to details
Excellent written and oral English and Chinese, Mandarin preferred
We offer attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits to the right candidate. Interested applicants please send detailed resume stating present & expected salaries and date of availability to Human Resources Department by clicking "APPLY NOW".

Further information about our group companies can be found at www.gfgroup.com.hk and www.gf.com.cn.

All applications will be treated in the strictest confidence and personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Responsibilities

Support Senior Management in all aspects of business and administration, coordination and communication with headquarters in executing Group business strategies to Hong Kong office as a subsidiary of the Group;
In charge of independent management meeting arrangement and prepare agenda, meeting materials and post-meeting minutes;
Responsible for coordinating business requests via the internal OA system, and maintain OA system’s daily operation;
Responsible for drafting and consolidating management reports for management perusal;
Provide internal departmental support, such as announcement of company rules and regulations, company important notice to staff;
Assist in projects for GF corporate branding;
Assist in ad-hoc projects assigned by Company Senior Management.
Requirement

Degree holder in Business Administration, Finance, Economics or relevant discipline;
3 - 4 years’ relevant experience in financial institutions, preferably in PRC-based investment banking;
Excellent command of both written and spoken English and Chinese; fluency in Putonghua is preferred;
Proficient in MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint & Outlook;
Strong self-motivation and able to work independently within tight timeline;
Good communication, interpersonal and presentation skills;
Ability to work in fast-paced environment with strong team spirit.
We offer attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits to the right candidate. Interested applicants please send detailed resume stating present & expected salaries and date of availability to Human Resources Department by clicking "APPLY NOW". 

Further information about our group companies can be found at www.gfgroup.com.hk and www.gf.com.cn. 

All applications will be treated in the strictest confidence and personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Responsibilities

Lead the team in execution of corporate finance transactions, including but not limited to IPO, Financial advisory and corporate finance related transactions;
Lead the team in liaising with professional parties and relevant authorities, such as SFC and Hong Kong Stock Exchange in connection with execution of projects;
Be actively involved in due diligence, market research, financial analysis and regulatory check; 
Supervise preparation of pitching materials
Requirements

At least 6 years’ working experience in corporate finance, preferably with focus in HK IPO execution;
Good analytical and interpersonal skills with a proven track record in executing IPOs;
Well versed with Listing Rules and Takeovers Code;
Proficiency in both written and spoken English and Chinese, fluency in Putonghua;
Able to work under pressure, self-motivated and a good team player.
We offer attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits to the right candidate. Interested applicants please send detailed resume stating present & expected salaries and date of availability to Human Resources Department by clicking "APPLY NOW".

Further information about our group companies can be found at www.gfgroup.com.hk and www.gf.com.cn.

All applications will be treated in the strictest confidence and personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Responsibilities:

Review and evaluate business proposals of bond investment and structured products including TRS, Leveraged Note and cross-border transactions, negotiate with business on the risk management requirements;
Conduct credit analysis of counterparties and issuers of underlying securities;
Review and confirm the internal credit rating of counterparties/bond issuers;
Keep close attention on risk incidents and adverse market news, evaluate the potential risks and provide warnings/risk mitigation suggestions to business;
Work closely with relevant parties to enhance the functionality and stability of the risk reporting system;
Compose/update internal risk management report on regular basis or upon request.
Requirements:

Bachelor Degree or above major in Business, Science or Engineering;
At least 5 years’ experience in financial institutions with exposures to offshore Fixed Income/Equity market and structured products. 
Professional qualifications, such as CFA / FRM / CPA will be an advantage;
Proficiency in MS Office is a must;
Detail-oriented and sensitive to numbers;
Good communication skills, fluent in Putonghua, proficient in Chinese writing.
Candidates with less experience will be considered for Associate position.
We offer attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits to the right candidate. Interested applicants please send detailed resume stating present & expected salaries and date of availability to Human Resources Department by clicking "APPLY NOW".

Further information about our group companies can be found at www.gfgroup.com.hk and www.gf.com.cn.

All applications will be treated in the strictest confidence and personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

As the leading financial advisory firm in Hong Kong, Convoy upholds its core values of Passion, Integrity and Professionalism in providing the best advices and service to help customers investing in their future.

Due to our business expansion, we are looking for high calibre candidates to share our vision and venture our success.


Responsibilities: 

Provide service to sales force to achieve company targets
Build good working relationships with business partners
Provide professional advice and broking service to sales force and clients to ensure the service excellence and customer retentions;
Handle and follow up on quotation, product selection, insurance policy issuing, underwriting, renewals, policy changes, claims service and premium matters;
Liaise between service providers on policy premium and product coverage; Assist on premium collection with sales force/clients
Review and verify application documents are in compliance with the requirements;
Perform ad hoc assignments and projects if necessary.

Requirements:

University graduate with hands on experience in managing general insurance business portfolio;
Qualifications in IIQE preferred;
Minimum 5 years’ working experience in insurance administration support and client servicing;
Energetic, self-disciplined with strong sense of responsibility, well-organized, detail-minded and can work independently;
Good communication skills with good command of both written and spoken in Cantonese, Mandarin and English;
Proficient in computer software for day-to-day operations.

We offer competitive remuneration including career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send detailed resume with availability, current and expected salaries to Human Resources Department, Convoy Global Holdings Limited, Trust Tower, 68 Johnston Road, Wan Chai, Hong Kong or by clicking the Apply Now button and upload your CV and cover letter.

(All applications will be treated in strict confidence and used for recruitment purpose within Convoy Global Holdings Limited only. All applicants are kept on file 6 months from the date of the application.)

