Job Responsibilities:

Assist in risk management and perform advisory assignments;
Assist in prepare regular reporting on capital, local solvency, ORSA and HKRBC etc.;
Conduct comprehensive data analysis, provide accurate results during reporting and forecasts;
Handle ad-hoc projects and other duties as required.

Job Requirements:

Bachelor Degree in Actuarial Science, Finance, Risk Management, Mathematics or Statistics, or related disciplines;
Proficient in MS Office and computer programming;
1-2 years actuarial experience;
Good analytical skills;
Good communication and interpersonal competencies;
Attention to details;
Willing to work under pressure and deadlines.



 We offer competitive remuneration package. Interested parties, please send your resume with CURRENT & EXPECTED salary and DATE AVAILABLE by clicking 'Apply Now'.

