Job Responsibilities:

Assess and process claims within delegated claims authority in accordance with the established procedures and guidelines;
Support the implementation of claims management strategies and objectives;
Reach benchmark of claims processing volume and turnaround time;
Assist in handling enquiries or complaints from internal and external customers;
Identify and conduct thorough investigation of suspicious cases, including report to superior; and
Handle ad-hoc duties as assigned by superior(s).

Job Requirements:

Colleague graduated or above;
3 years' relevant experience in insurance industry, preferably in medical claims;
Professional qualification in FLMI, FLHC, etc. will be an advantage;
Familiar with operation of medical claims and healthcare network providers;
Good communication and interpersonal skills;
Flexible and customer-oriented;
Detail-minded with strong sense of responsibilities and well-organized;
Able to handle multi-task and work under pressure in a fact paced enviornment;
Good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese; and
Proficient in MS Office and Chinese Word Processing.
We offer excellent career prospects and attractive remuneration package including 5-day work week, year-end bonus, life, medical and dental coverage, birthday leave, volunteer leave, well-being time off, etc.

Please submit your application via our Company’s Career Opportunities webpage.  Personal Data provided by applicants will only be used for recruitment purposes and be handled in accordance with the Company's Privacy Policy Statement, which is available on our website. Applicants who are not contacted for interview within six (6) weeks may consider their application unsuccessful. The Company will retain the applications for a maximum period of six (6) months and may reconsider the applicants for other suitable vacancies within the Company, where appropriate.
